INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Waterfronts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter in relation to the department of city planning.
EventItemMatterName: City Planning Commission.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the City of New York, in relation exit path markings in high-rise buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Exit path markings in high-rise buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the City of New York, in relation to the installation and upgrade of parking meter technology.
EventItemMatterName: Installation and upgrade of parking meter technology.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the City of New York, in relation to allowing parking at missing or broken meters or muni-meters up to the maximum time permitted in that parking meter zone.
EventItemMatterName: Allowing parking at missing or broken meters or muni-meters up to the maximum time permitted in that parking meter zone.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Metropolitan Transit Authority and the New York City Department of Transportation to coordinate payment technology so that all muni-meter parking cards are compatible with the city’s transit fare technology.
EventItemMatterName: MTA and the NYC Dept of Transportation to coordinate payment technology so that all muni-meter parking cards are compatible with the city’s transit fare technology.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the City of New York, in relation to creating a public online database regarding violations incurred by businesses that operate delivery bicycles.
EventItemMatterName: Creating a public online database regarding violations incurred by businesses that operate delivery bicycles.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution granting additional real property tax exemptions for certain affordable housing developments.
EventItemMatterName: Granting additional real property tax exemptions for certain affordable housing developments.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the transfer of general vending licenses.
EventItemMatterName: Transfer of general vending licenses.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Parks and Recreation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to renaming one thoroughfare in the Borough of Manhattan, River Terrace, and to amend the official map of the city of New York accordingly.
EventItemMatterName: Renaming one thoroughfare in the Borough of Manhattan, River Terrace, and to amend the official map of the city of New York accordingly.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter and the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of education and the police department to provide information regarding school discipline and school safety agents to the city council.
EventItemMatterName: CCRB  to investigate complaints of misconduct by police personnel assigned to public schools.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Housing Authority to review its infrastructure and address a possible correlation between air vents, water pipes and asthma, which may result in an increase in asthma among its residents.
EventItemMatterName: NYCHA to review its infrastructure and address a possible correlation between air vents, water pipes and asthma, which may result in an increase in asthma among its residents.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon Animal Care and Control of New York City to establish a citywide Trap, Neuter, and Return program for feral animals.
EventItemMatterName: Establish a citywide Trap, Neuter, and Return program for feral animals.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Senate to pass S.4614-A, which would help protect children from sexual predators.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Senate to pass S.4614-A, which would help protect children from sexual predators.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the City of New York, in relation to requiring instruction and testing on information concerning food allergies as part of the food protection course.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring instruction and testing on information concerning food allergies as part of the food protection course.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring posters with information on food allergy in food service establishments.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring posters with information on food allergies in food service establishments.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Department of Education and the School Construction Authority to implement changes to reform city school planning to better address the problem of overcrowding.
EventItemMatterName: Department of Education and School Construction Authority to implement changes to reform city school planning.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to enact legislation amending the New York State Penal Law to include penalties for police officers prematurely leaving the scene of a crime or shooting without reporting the incident as soon as practicable.
EventItemMatterName: Penal Law to include penalties for police officers prematurely leaving the scene of a crime or shooting without reporting the incident as soon as practicable.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter and the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring financial reports for real property acquired by the city through eminent domain.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring financial reports for real property acquired by the city through eminent domain.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of New York State Assembly Bill 4022 an act to amend the public authorities law, the not-for-profit corporation law, the general municipal law and the public authorities law, in relation to eminent domain reform; and creating the “home and property protection act” providing for the creation of a temporary state commission to examine eminent domain laws and make recommendations for further reforms; and making an appropriation therefore; and providing for the expiration of certain provisions.
EventItemMatterName: Eminent domain reform; and creating the “home and property protection act” providing for the creation of a temporary state commission to examine eminent domain laws and make recommendations for further reforms (A.4022).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of New York State Assembly Bill A 9676 an act to amend the eminent domain procedure law, in relation to creating additional requirements before allowing eminent domain for the use of private developers
EventItemMatterName: Eminent domain procedure law, in relation to creating additional requirements before allowing eminent domain for the use of private developers (A.9676).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of New York State Assembly Bill A 1388 an act to amend the eminent domain procedure law, in relation to requiring new hearings when public projects using eminent domain are altered or amended.
EventItemMatterName: Eminent domain procedure law, in relation to requiring new hearings when public projects using eminent domain are altered or amended (A.1388).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of New York State Assembly Bill A 1265 and New York State Senate companion Bill S 683 which would provide for the creation of a temporary state commission to examine eminent domain laws and to make recommendations for reforms.
EventItemMatterName: Provide for the creation of a temporary state commission to examine eminent domain laws and to make recommendations for reforms (A.1265/S.683).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of New York State Assembly Bill A 1264 and New York State Senate companion Bill S 688 which would amend the public authorities law, the not-for-profit corporation law, the general municipal law and which would reform the use of eminent domain.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the public authorities law, the not-for-profit corporation law, the general municipal law and which would reform the use of eminent domain (A.1264/S.688).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of New York State Senate Bill S 4769 which would amend the public authorities law, in relation to providing cities with a population of one million or more a greater role in the use by public authorities of eminent domain within their borders.
EventItemMatterName: Providing cities with a population of one million or more a greater role in the use by public authorities of eminent domain within their borders (S.4769).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of New York State Assembly Bill A 661-A and New York State Senate companion Bill S 915-A an act to amend the eminent domain procedure law, in relation to the use of eminent domain only for public projects, approval of the use of eminent domain by the governing body when the condemnor is an industrial development agency and the requirement that the condemnor pay relocation costs.
EventItemMatterName: Use of eminent domain only for public projects, approval of the use of eminent domain by the governing body when the condemnor is an industrial development agency and the requirement that the condemnor pay relocation costs (A.661-A/S.915-A).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling for a federal investigation into the issuance of an emergency passport to a Serbian national who fled the United States during a pending court case, urging the Serbian government to extradite such fugitive and requesting that the federal government improve procedures regarding access to emergency passports for non-citizens attempting to leave the United States.
EventItemMatterName: Federal investigation into the issuance of an emergency passport to a Serbian national who fled the US during a pending court case, urging the Serbian government to extradite such fugitive.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to placing a cap on the number of misdemeanor and felony cases an attorney can handle in representing indigent defendants.
EventItemMatterName: Placing a cap on the number of misdemeanor and felony cases an attorney can handle in representing indigent defendants.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Rights
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Federal Communications Commission to investigate Arbitron's Portable People Meter system and its potential effect on the diversity of radio.
EventItemMatterName: Federal Communications Commission to investigate Arbitron's Personal People Meter system and its potential effect on the diversity of radio.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the New York State Legislature to more clearly and narrowly define “public use, benefit or purpose” in the State Eminent Domain Procedure Law.
EventItemMatterName: State Legislature to more clearly and narrowly define “public use, benefit or purpose” in the State Eminent Domain Procedure Law.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Aging
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing public notice for senior center closings.
EventItemMatterName: Providing public notice for senior center closings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Fiscal 2009 Expense Budget.
EventItemMatterName: Disclosing the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Fiscal 2009 Expense Budget.
